# Controller error handling

Controllers orchestrate integrations; they must **not** swallow upstream failures as success or silent fallbacks.

## Status codes

| Situation | Status | Client body |
|-----------|--------|-------------|
| Success | `200` | Normal payload |
| Legitimate empty result (news search OK, zero articles) | `204` | Empty body |
| Upstream unavailable / rate limit (Finnhub 429, Replicate 422/503, etc.) | `503` | `{ "error": "...", "integration": "finnhub" \| "replicate" }` |
| All social targets failed to post | `502` | `{ "error": "...", "integration": "social" }` |
| No usable data after partial upstream success (e.g. zero quotes) | `500` | `{ "error": "...", "integration": "finnhub" }` |
| Unexpected throw | `500` | `{ "error": "...", "integration": "..." }` |

Use helpers in `src/http/errors.ts` (`logIntegrationError`, `respondUpstreamUnavailable`, etc.).

## Logging

- **`console.error`** for integration failures (include route prefix: `[news]`, `[stocks]`).
- Log **provider name** and **response detail** when the SDK exposes it (axios `response.data`, twitter-api-v2 `data`).
- **`console.warn`** only for expected soft cases (e.g. single ticker quote miss on stocks when others succeed).

## Do not

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — rate limit becomes 204
catch (err) {
  if (isRateLimited(err)) return undefined
}

// ❌ BAD — LLM failure hidden; posts raw headline as if success
catch { comment = news.headline }

// ❌ BAD — all fanout failed but client gets 200
res.status(200).json({ created_at: now })
```

## Do

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — distinguish empty vs upstream down
if (outcome.status === "empty") return res.sendStatus(204)
if (outcome.status === "rate_limited") {
  return respondUpstreamUnavailable(res, "finnhub", "Finnhub rate limit exceeded")
}

// ✅ GOOD — partial fan-out still 200 (fail-soft on posting)
const posts = await fanout(message, targets)
if (!fanoutHadSuccess(posts)) return respondSocialPublishFailed(res, posts)
res.status(200).json(buildPostApiResponse(now, posts))
```

## Scope

- **Fan-out:** one platform failing → still `200` if another succeeded (north-star fail-soft).
- **Domain fallbacks** (e.g. holiday list when Finnhub calendar fails) stay in domain/services, not controllers.
- Update `docs/API.md` when response codes or error bodies change.
